This paper deals with the computational complexity of solving stochastic games, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the polynomial time equivalence of different tasks, which involves algorithmic analysis and complexity theory (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper proposes algorithms for solving these games, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper uses mathematical analysis to prove its results, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG).
